# VibeCraft — Epic Fantasy Knight Fighter
#
# Generated following classical art guide principles for drawing humanoids:
#   - Loomis 7.5-head proportional canon (7.5 head-units tall)
#   - Contrapposto stance with hip/shoulder counter-tilt
#   - S-curve spine for natural, alive posture
#   - Ribcage and pelvis as distinct tilted volumes
#   - Bold separated armor plates with gold accents
#   - Strong silhouette readable from all angles
#   - Asymmetric pose (sword raised right, shield held left)
#   - Gesture/line of action flowing through the figure
#
# Reference guides consulted:
#   - "Figure Drawing for All It's Worth" by Andrew Loomis (proportion system)
#   - doncorgi.com/blog/how-to-draw-human-proportions (head-unit method)
#   - skyryedesign.com/tutorials/how-to-draw-human (gesture & contrapposto)
#   - en.zephy.fr/blog/drawing-human-body-proportions (proportional landmarks)
#   - coohom.com/article/how-to-pose-3d-models-effectively (avoiding stiffness)
#   - tips.clip-studio.com/en-us/articles/7734 (dynamic poses)
#   - finearttutorials.com/guide/figure-drawing (figure drawing basics)
#
#
# 753 vertices, 1116 triangles
# Dimensions: ~2.0 units tall body, sword tip at ~Y=3.0
#
# Convention: Y-up, right-handed coordinate system

mtllib fighter.mtl

